paragraphs.title: Création table
paragraphs.text:
%spark

//sqlContext.setConf("hive.metastore.warehouse.dir", "/tmp/hive")

val df = sqlContext.read.format("com.databricks.spark.csv").
    option("header", "true").
    option("delimiter", ",").
    option("quote", "\"").
    option("mode", "PERMISSIVE").
    option("charset", "UTF-8").
    option("inferSchema", "true").
    load("/data/IRVE-201510.csv")

sqlContext.sql("drop table bornes")
df.write.saveAsTable("bornes")

paragraphs.text:

SELECT source, count(1) AS nb_stations FROM bornes GROUP BY source ORDER BY nb_stations DESC

paragraphs.title: Init data pour map
paragraphs.text:
val gson = new com.google.gson.Gson()
val bornes = sqlContext.sql("select adresse_station, observations, type_connecteur, latitude, longitude from bornes where longitude is not null and latitude is not null").
    map { r => Map( 
        "adresse" -> r(0).toString,
        "observations" -> r(1).toString,
        "connecteur" -> r(2).toString,
        "latitude" -> r(3).toString.toDouble,
        "longitude" -> r(4).toString.toDouble
    )}.
    collect.map(s => scala.collection.JavaConversions.mapAsJavaMap(s))
val jsonBornes = gson.toJson(bornes)
